### Get table [GET /apps/{app_id}/tables/{table_id}]

Get one table of the application.

+ Parameters 
    + app_id (string) - ID or internal name of the application
    + table_id (string) - ID of the table

+ Response 200

    + Attributes
        + data (Table) - Table object

    + Body

            { 
                "data": {
                    "id": "2252d3ce-0bce-44fa-b8d6-1e0ab1f0c277",
                    "shortid": "xbo9aya392",
                    "header": "Customers",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "id": "firstname",
                            "header": "Firstname",
                            "type": "text",
                            "metadata": {
                                "description": "Firstname of customer",
                                "maxLength": 100,
                                "required": true
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "surname",
                            "header": "Surname",
                            "type": "text",
                            "metadata": {
                                "description": "Surname of customer",
                                "maxLength": 100,
                                "required": true
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "age",
                            "header": "Age",
                            "type": "number",
                            "metadata": {
                                "description": "Age of customer",
                                "min": 18,
                                "max": 99,
                                "required": false
                            }
                        }
                    ],
                    "settings": {
                        "userFilters": [
                            {
                                "id": "xil9gznz16",
                                "name": "New Customers",
                                "description": "New Customers",
                                "visibility": "global"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "scripts": [
                        { 
                            "name": "onModelLoad",
                            "script": "doo.model.<[Firstname (firstname)]>.value = 'John';"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            }

## Records [/apps/{app_id}/tables/{table_id}/data{?limit,skip,sort,filter}]
Resources for CRUD operations with data.

+ Parameters
    + app_id (string, required) - ID of the application
    + table_id (string) - ID of the table
    + limit (optional, number) - The number of records returned in each request. Accepts any value between 0 and 1000.
        + Default: `25`
    + skip (optional, number) - Which record in the list to start from. The value should be greater than or equal to 0.
        + Default: `0`
    + sort (optional, string) - A list of sort table fields which are used to sort the retrieved record. 
    Simple sorting - ``sort=age``, Multi sorting - ``sort=age,surname(desc)``
    + filter (optional, string) - Filter condition (where condition). 
    Simple filter - ``filter=age(gte)10``, 
    Multi filter - ``filter=age(gte)10,surname(eq)Fox``, 
    Filter with multivalues - ``filter=surname(in)(Fox,Dog,text with \\, comma)``
        + Members
            + `contains`
            + `notcontains`
            + `startswith`
            + `endswith`
            + `eq`
            + `===`
            + `neq`
            + `empty`
            + `notempty`
            + `in`
            + `notin`
            + `gt`
            + `lt`
            + `gte`
            + `lte`
            + `duplicity`
            + `currentuser`

### Get List of data [GET]
**[GET]** 

To receive the list of data from a table.

For more information on filters, [click here](#introduction/filters).

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes 
        + data (array[Record]) - Array of data/records

    + Body
        
            { 
                "data": [
                    {
                        "id": "158cb6ef-02a6-47dc-8134-188c1b6426e6",
                        "created": "2019-03-22T14:41:23.5783244+00:00",
                        "modified": "2019-03-24T16:31:28.5783244+00:00",
                        "ver": 0,
                        "fields": {
                            "firstname": "John",
                            "surname": "Snow",
                            "age": 35
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "8095b72f-5642-4a75-b4f7-5ba11da65ea2",
                        "created": "2019-03-22T14:41:23.5783244+00:00",
                        "modified": "2019-03-24T16:31:28.5783244+00:00",
                        "ver": 0,
                        "fields": {
                            "firstname": "Peter",
                            "surname": "Parker",
                            "age": 28
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "8905f3aa-97df-4c0b-b10f-d5fe3bcd6979",
                        "created": "2019-03-22T14:41:23.5783244+00:00",
                        "modified": "2019-03-24T16:31:28.5783244+00:00",
                        "ver": 2,
                        "fields": {
                            "firstname": "Jack",
                            "surname": "Reacher",
                            "age": 42
                        }
                    }
                ]
            }

### Get List of data (filter) [POST /apps/{app_id}/tables/{table_id}/data/filter{?limit,skip,sort}]
**[POST]**

To receive the list of data from a table with filter conditions sending in the body.

You can also specify which fields should be loaded using the ``loadFields`` parameter. If not provided, all fields will be returned.

For more information on filters, [click here](#introduction/filters).

+ Request 

    + `loadFields` (optional) - load only specific fields
    + `filter` (optional) - for more information on filters [click here](#introduction/filters)

    + Body 
    
            {
                "filter": [
                    { 
                        "field": "age",
                        "operator": "gte",
                        "value": "30"
                    }   
                ],
                "loadFields": ["name", "age"]
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes 
        + data (array[Record]) - Array of data/records

    + Body
        
            { 
                "data": [
                    {
                        "id": "158cb6ef-02a6-47dc-8134-188c1b6426e6",
                        "created": "2019-03-22T14:41:23.5783244+00:00",
                        "modified": "2019-03-24T16:31:28.5783244+00:00",
                        "ver": 0,
                        "fields": {
                            "firstname": "John",
                            "surname": "Snow",
                            "age": 35
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "8905f3aa-97df-4c0b-b10f-d5fe3bcd6979",
                        "created": "2019-03-22T14:41:23.5783244+00:00",
                        "modified": "2019-03-24T16:31:28.5783244+00:00",
                        "ver": 2,
                        "fields": {
                            "firstname": "Jack",
                            "surname": "Reacher",
                            "age": 42
                        }
                    }
                ]
            }

### Get count of data [GET /apps/{app_id}/tables/{table_id}/data/count{?filter}]
**[GET]**

Get the number of records in the table.

For more information on filters, [click here](#introduction/filters).

Example request: 

``https://app.tabidoo.cloud/v2/apps/158cb6ef/tables/8095b72f/data/count``


+ Response 200

    + Attributes 
        + data - Count object
            + count: 3 (number) - Count of records

    + Body
        
            { 
                "data": {
                        "count": 3
                }
            }

### Get count of data (filter) [POST /apps/{app_id}/tables/{table_id}/data/count/filter]
**[POST]**

Get the number of records in the table with filter conditions sending in the body.

For more information about filters, [click here](#introduction/filters).

+ Request 

    + Body 
    
            {
                "filter": [
                    { 
                        "field": "age",
                        "operator": "gte",
                        "value": "30"
                    }   
                ]
            }

+ Response 200

    + Attributes 
        + data - Count object
            + count: 3 (number) - Count of records

    + Body
        
            { 
                "data": {
                        "count": 3
                }
            }

### Get data summary [POST /apps/{app_id}/tables/{table_id}/data/summary]
**[POST]**

Get summary data from a table with filter conditions and required aggregations (min/max/sum/avg for numbers and min/max for date-time) sending in the body.
Only number and date/date-time fields are supported. Aggregations min/max/sum/avg are supported for numbers. Aggregations min/max are supported for date/date-time.

For more information about filters, [click here](#introduction/filters).

+ Request 

    + Body 
    
            {
                "filter": [
                    { 
                        "field": "age",
                        "operator": "gte",
                        "value": "30"
                    }   
                ],
                "fields": {
                    "age": { aggregations: ["min", "max", "sum", "avg"] },
                    "dateOfBirth": { aggregations: ["min", "max"] },
                    "someNumber": { aggregations: ["avg"] },
                    "dateOfEmployment": { aggregations: ["min"] }
                }
            }

+ Response 200

    + Attributes 
        + data - Summary object
            + count: 3 (number) - Count of records
            + fields (object) - Dynamic object of aggregated fields

    + Body
        
            { 
                "data": {
                    "count": 3,
                    "fields": {
                        "age": {
                            "min": 31,
                            "max": 44,
                            "sum": 111,
                            "avg": 37,
                        },
                        "dateOfBirth": {
                            "min": "1980-05-23T00:00:00Z",
                            "max": "1994-07-03T00:00:00Z",
                        },
                        "someNumber": {
                            "avg": 24
                        },
                        "dateOfEmployment": {
                            "avg": "2002-11-11T12:34:56Z"
                        }
                    }
                }
            }

### Get data record [GET /apps/{app_id}/tables/{table_id}/data/{record_id}]
**[GET]**

To retrieve a single record.

+ Parameters
    + record_id (string) - ID of data record

+ Response 200

