### Create data record [POST /apps/{app_id}/tables/{table_id}/data{?dataResponseType}]
**[POST]**

Creates a new record in a specific Tabidoo table.

This endpoint supports **UPSERT** mode - see the **useUpsert** parameter.

+ Parameters
    + dataResponseType (optional, string) - Data response type. *None* - no data is returned, *MetadataOnly* - only metadata is returned, *All* - all fields of the record

+ Request

    + Body
    
            { 
                "fields": {
                    "firstname": "John",
                    "surname": "Snow",
                    "age": 35
                }
            }

+ Response 201

    + Attributes
        + data (Record) - Record object

    + Body
    
            {
                "data": {
                    "id": "158cb6ef-02a6-47dc-8134-188c1b6426e6",
                    "created": "2019-03-22T14:41:23.5783244+00:00",
                    "modified": "2019-03-22T14:41:23.5783244+00:00",
                    "ver": 0,
                    "fields": {
                        "firstname": "John",
                        "surname": "Snow",
                        "age": 35
                    }
                }
            }

### Update data record (PARTIAL) [PATCH /apps/{app_id}/tables/{table_id}/data/{record_id}{?dataResponseType}]
**[PATCH]**

Updates an existing record in a specific Tabidoo table. 

This endpoint supports **UPSERT** mode - see the **useUpsert** parameter.

This is a **PARTIAL update** - it only updates the fields that are sent.

**TIP** - [Upsert mode](#introduction/parameters/upsert-mode).

+ Parameters
    + record_id (string) - ID of data record
    + dataResponseType (optional, string) - Data response type. *None* - no data is returned, *MetadataOnly* - only metadata is returned, *All* - all fields of the record
    
+ Request

    + Body
    
            { 
                "fields": {
                    "age": 39
                }
            }

+ Response 200
    
    + Attributes
        + data (Record) - Record object

    + Body
    
            {
                "data": {
                    "id": "158cb6ef-02a6-47dc-8134-188c1b6426e6",
                    "created": "2019-03-22T14:41:23.5783244+00:00",
                    "modified": "2019-03-25T17:22:26.5783244+00:00",
                    "ver": 1,
                    "fields": {
                        "firstname": "John",
                        "surname": "Snow",
                        "age": 39
                    }
                }
            }

### Update data record (FULL) [PUT /apps/{app_id}/tables/{table_id}/data/{record_id}{?dataResponseType}]
**[PUT]**

Updates an existing record in a specific Tabidoo table. 

This endpoint supports **UPSERT** mode - see the **useUpsert** parameter.

This is a **FULL update** - it replaces the whole record with sent fields, thus unsent fields are deleted.

**TIP** - [Upsert mode](#introduction/parameters/upsert-mode).

+ Parameters
    + record_id (string) - ID of data record
    + dataResponseType (optional, string) - Data response type. *None* - no data is returned, *MetadataOnly* - only metadata is returned, *All* - all fields of the record
    
+ Request

    + Body
    
            { 
                "fields": {
                    "firstname": "Jack",
                    "surname": "Snow",
                    "age": 41
                }
            }

+ Response 200

    + Attributes
        + data (Record) - Record object

    + Body
    
            {
                "data": {
                    "id": "158cb6ef-02a6-47dc-8134-188c1b6426e6",
                    "created": "2019-03-22T14:41:23.5783244+00:00",
                    "modified": "2019-03-25T17:22:26.5783244+00:00",
                    "ver": 2,
                    "fields": {
                        "firstname": "Jack",
                        "surname": "Snow",
                        "age": 41
                    }
                }
            }

### Delete data record [DELETE /apps/{app_id}/tables/{table_id}/data/{record_id}]
**[DELETE]**

Deletes a single record in a specific Tabidoo table.

+ Parameters
    + record_id (string) - ID of data record
    
+ Response 204

## Records - bulk [/apps/{app_id}/tables/{table_id}/data/bulk{?dataResponseType}]
Resources for bulk operations with data.

+ Parameters
    + app_id (string, required) - ID of the application
    + table_id (string) - ID of the table
    + dataResponseType (optional, string) - Data response type. *None* - no data are returned, *MetadataOnly* - Only metadata are returned

### Create data records - bulk [POST /apps/{app_id}/tables/{table_id}/data/bulk{?dataResponseType}]
**[POST]**

Creates records in a specific Tabidoo table.

This endpoint supports **UPSERT** mode - see the **useUpsert** parameter.
In **UPSERT** mode, some records can be inserted and some can be updated.

**TIP** - [Data response type](#introduction/parameters/data-response-type).

+ Parameters
    + dataResponseType (optional, string) - Data response type. *None* - no data is returned, *MetadataOnly* - only metadata is returned

+ Request

    + Body
    
            {
                "bulk": [
                            {
                                "fields": {
                                    "firstname": "Jack",
                                    "surname": "Newman"
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "fields": {
                                    "firstname": "Peter",
                                    "surname": "Novak"
                                }
                            }
                ]
            }

+ Response 200

    This example shows that two records were inserted.

    In **UPSERT** mode, some records can be inserted and some can be updated.

    + Body
    
            {
                "bulk": {
                    "successCount": 2,
                    "insertedCount": 2
                },
                "data": [
                    {
                        "id": "158cb6ef-02a6-47dc-8134-188c1b6426e6",
                        "created": "2019-03-22T14:41:23.5783244+00:00",
                        "modified": "2019-03-25T17:22:26.5783244+00:00",
                        "ver": 0,
                        "fields": {
                            "firstname": "Jack",
                            "surname": "Newman"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "2f64141a-ec9f-43df-a50d-1ca8eb277df7",
                        "created": "2019-03-22T14:41:23.5783244+00:00",
                        "modified": "2019-03-25T17:22:26.5783244+00:00",
                        "ver": 0,
                        "fields": {
                            "firstname": "Peter",
                            "surname": "Novak"
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "errors": [
                    {
                        "type": "string",
                        "id": "string",
                        "message": "string"
                    }
                ]
            }
            
### Update data records - bulk (PARTIAL) [PATCH /apps/{app_id}/tables/{table_id}/data/bulk{?dataResponseType}]
**[PATCH]**

Updates records in a specific Tabidoo table.

This endpoint supports **UPSERT** mode - see the **useUpsert** parameter.
In **UPSERT** mode, some records can be inserted and some can be updated.

This is a **PARTIAL update** - it only updates the fields that are sent.

**WARN** - If the id is empty or the record is not found in the table, the record is ignored/skipped without reporting.

**TIP** - [Upsert mode](#introduction/parameters/upsert-mode).

+ Parameters
    + dataResponseType (optional, string) - Data response type. *None* - no data is returned, *MetadataOnly* - only metadata is returned

+ Request

    + Body
    
            {
                "bulk": [
                            {
                                "id": "158cb6ef-02a6-47dc-8134-188c1b6426e6",
                                "fields": {
                                    
                                    "firstname": "Jack",
                                    "surname": "Newman"
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "id": "2f64141a-ec9f-43df-a50d-1ca8eb277df7",
                                "fields": {
                                    "firstname": "Peter",
                                    "surname": "Novak"
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "id": "abdf9ff3-4b1a-42ae-92df-d394577354f7",
                                "fields": {
                                    "firstname": "Lucas",
                                    "surname": "Pear"
                                }
                            }
                ]
            }

+ Response 200

    This example shows that three records were sent for bulk update, two recorde were updated and one record was not updated (it was unchanged or it does not exist).
    
    In **UPSERT** mode, some records can be inserted and some can be updated.

    + Body
    
            {
                "bulk": {
                    "successCount": 3,
                    "insertedCount": 0,
                    "updatedCount": 2
                },
                "data": [
                    {
                        "id": "158cb6ef-02a6-47dc-8134-188c1b6426e6",
                        "created": "2019-03-22T14:41:23.5783244+00:00",
                        "modified": "2019-03-25T17:22:26.5783244+00:00",
                        "ver": 0,
                        "fields": {
                            "firstname": "Jack",
                            "surname": "Newman"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "2f64141a-ec9f-43df-a50d-1ca8eb277df7",
                        "created": "2019-03-22T14:41:23.5783244+00:00",
                        "modified": "2019-03-25T17:22:26.5783244+00:00",
                        "ver": 0,
                        "fields": {
                            "firstname": "Peter",
                            "surname": "Novak"
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "errors": [
                    {
                        "type": "string",
                        "id": "string",
                        "message": "string"
                    }
                ]
            }
            
### Update data records - bulk (FULL) [PUT /apps/{app_id}/tables/{table_id}/data/bulk{?dataResponseType}]
**[PUT]**

Updates records in a specific Tabidoo table.

This endpoint supports **UPSERT** mode - see the **useUpsert** parameter.
In **UPSERT** mode, some records can be inserted and some can be updated.

This is a **FULL update** - it replaces the whole record with sent fields, thus unsent fields are deleted.

**WARN** - If the id is empty or the record is not found in the table, the record is ignored/skipped without reporting.

**TIP** - [Upsert mode](#introduction/parameters/upsert-mode).

+ Parameters
    + dataResponseType (optional, string) - Data response type. *None* - no data is returned, *MetadataOnly* - only metadata is returned

+ Request

    + Body
    
            {
                "bulk": [
                            {
                                "id": "c7609e47-a63c-4d6a-a4c3-3d8253dbf443",
                                "fields": {
                                    "firstname": "Jack",
                                    "surname": "Newman"
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "id": "2f64141a-ec9f-43df-a50d-1ca8eb277df7",
                                "fields": {
                                    "firstname": "Peter",
                                    "surname": "Novak"
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "id": "abdf9ff3-4b1a-42ae-92df-d394577354f7",
                                "fields": {
                                    "firstname": "Thomas",
                                    "surname": "Pear"
                                }
                            }
                ]
            }

+ Response 200

    This example shows that three records were sent for bulk update, two recorde were updated and one record was not updated (it was unchanged or it does not exist).
    
    In **UPSERT** mode, some records can be inserted and some can be updated.

    + Body
    
            {
                "bulk": {
                    "successCount": 3,
                    "insertedCount": 0,
                    "updatedCount": 2
                },
                "data": [
                    {
                        "id": "158cb6ef-02a6-47dc-8134-188c1b6426e6",
                        "created": "2019-03-22T14:41:23.5783244+00:00",
                        "modified": "2019-03-25T17:22:26.5783244+00:00",
                        "ver": 0,
                        "fields": {
                            "firstname": "Jack",
                            "surname": "Newman"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "2f64141a-ec9f-43df-a50d-1ca8eb277df7",
                        "created": "2019-03-22T14:41:23.5783244+00:00",
                        "modified": "2019-03-25T17:22:26.5783244+00:00",
                        "ver": 0,
                        "fields": {
                            "firstname": "Peter",
                            "surname": "Novak"
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "errors": [
                    {
                        "type": "string",
                        "id": "string",
                        "message": "string"
                    }
                ]
            }
            
### Delete data record - bulk [DELETE /apps/{app_id}/tables/{table_id}/data/bulk{?limit,filter}]
**[DELETE]**

Deletes data records in a specific Tabidoo table.

Bulk delete request requires the "Limit" query string parameter. Bulk delete can use condition filters located in the query string.

+ Parameters
    + limit (number) - The number of records to delete. Accepts any value between 1 and 2147483647.
    + filter (optional, string) - Filter condition (where condition). 
    Simple filter - ``filter=age(gte)10``, 
    Multi filter - ``filter=age(gte)10,surname(eq)Fox``, 
    Filter with multivalues - ``filter=surname(in)(Fox,Dog,text with \\, comma)``
        + Members
            + `contains`
            + `notcontains`
            + `startswith`
            + `endswith`
            + `eq`
            + `===`
            + `neq`
            + `empty`
            + `notempty`
            + `in`
            + `notin`
            + `gt`
            + `lt`
            + `gte`
            + `lte`
            + `duplicity`
            + `currentuser`
    
+ Response 204

## Files/Images [/apps/{app_id}/tables/{table_id}/files/{file_id}{?token}]

Resources for getting files/images and their thumbnails. 

*For uploading files/images use standard resources **Create data record** and **Update data record***.

[Find out more in the Fields section](#introduction/fields/picture/file).

### Get file [GET]

+ Parameters
    + app_id (string, required) - Application ID
    + table_id (string) - Table ID
    + file_id (string) - File ID
    + token (optional, string) - Security (short) token - *use if it is not possible to send an auth token in the HTTP request header.*

+ Response 200

+ Response 404

### Get image thumbnail [GET /apps/{app_id}/tables/{table_id}/files/{file_id}/thumbnail{?token}]

+ Parameters
    + app_id (string, required) - Application ID
    + table_id (string) - Table ID
    + file_id (string) - File ID
    + token (optional, string) - Security (short) token - *use if it is not possible to send an auth token in the HTTP request header.*

+ Response 200

+ Response 404

## Users [/users]
Resources for getting users info

### Current User Information [GET /users/me]
Resource allows an authenticated user to retrieve their own profile details, specifically the user ```id``` and ```email``` address. It is commonly used to confirm the currently logged-in user's identity.

+ Request 

    + Headers
            
            Authorization: Bearer <jwt-token>

+ Response 200

    + Attributes
        + id (string, required) - user's id
        + email (string, required) - user's email
        
    + Body
    
            {
                "data": 
                {
                    "id": "3352d3ce-0ace-44fa-b8d6-1e0ab1f0d789",
                    "email": "john.snow@tabidoo.cloud"
                }
            }


## Templates [/templates/createDevAppFromProdApp]

### Create a DEV app from PROD app [POST]
Allows you to create a development (DEV) application from an existing production (PROD) application. This is useful for introducing a proper development cycle (DEV → PROD), testing new features, and avoiding changes to live applications. 
For more information on templates, [click here](https://help.tabidoo.cloud/en/article/creating-a-development-app-from-a-production-app).

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + applicationId: `abc86445-048e-4ada-ae48-2ffd531cdcdc` (string) - The ID of the production application from which the DEV version should be created.
        + overrideExistingTemplateId (optional, string) - Use only if the PROD app was originally created from a template or already has a linked DEV app.

+ Response 200 (application/json)


# Data Structures

## ApplicationSimple (object)
+ id: `3352d3ce-0ace-44fa-b8d6-1e0ab1f0d78` (string) - Application id
+ name: `Task & Project Management` (string) - Application name
+ internalName: `taskAndProjectManagement` (string) - Internal name of the application

## Application (object)
+ id: `3352d3ce-0ace-44fa-b8d6-1e0ab1f0d78` (string) - Application id
+ name: `Task & Project Management` (string) - Application name
+ internalName: `taskAndProjectManagement` (string) - Internal name of the application
+ modules (array[Module]) - Modules of the application
+ tables (array[Table]) - Tables of the application

## Module (object)
+ shortId: default (string) - Short ID of the module
+ header: Default (string) - Header of the module
+ tableIds: `e641691e-426c-4e27-8760-47f491372962`, `c896587d-1aea-42ae-9944-f424729390a3` (array[string]) - array of table ids

## Table (object) 
+ id: `2252d3ce-0bce-44fa-b8d6-1e0ab1f0c277` (string) - Table ID
+ shortid: xbo9aya392 (string) - Table short id
+ internalNameApi: order (string) - Internal name of the table
+ header: Customers (string) - Table header
+ items (array[Field], optional) - Array of table fields
+ settings (object, optional) - Table settings
    + userFilters (array[object], optional) - Table view settings (predefined filters/view)
+ scripts (array[object], optional) - Array of the form scripts
    + name (string, required) - Name of script (onModelLoad, onModelChange, beforeModelSave, afterModelSave)
    + script (string, required) - Script

## Field (object)
+ name (string) - Field name
+ header (string) - Field header
+ type (string) - Data type of the field
+ metadata (Metadata, optional) - Field metadata

## Metadata (object)
+ description (string, optional) - Field description
+ required (boolean)
+ filterableFields: "id", "name"  (array[string], optional) - An array of filterable link fields (for link fields only).

## Record (object)
+ id: `2252d3ce-0bce-44fa-b8d6-1e0ab1f0c277` (string) - Record ID
+ created: `2019-03-22T14:41:23.5783244+00:00` (string) - The date the record was created
+ modified: `2019-03-24T16:31:28.5783244+00:00` (string) - Date of last modification of the record
+ ver: 0 (number) - Record version
+ fields (object) - Fields of the record (dynamic structure)

## Ping (object) 
+ message: Tabidoo ping OK (string) - Test message from Tabidoo
